The paper deals with assessing the performance of wireless systems using statistical techniques and data mining. This involves analyzing a large amount of simulation data to identify regions of the configuration space that exhibit acceptable performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistical inference (cs.SI).
